HEADWORD: Armistice
<hw>Ar"mis*tice</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>armistice</ets>, fr. (an assumed word) L. <ets>armistitium</ets>;
<ets>arma</ets> arms + <ets>stare</ets>, <ets>statum</ets> (combining
form, <ets>-stitum</ets>), to stand still.]</ety> <def>A cessation of
arms for a short time, by convention; a temporary suspension of
hostilities by agreement; a truce.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

